<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Reprove" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Reprove,</orth> 1) to disprove, to confute: <cit><quote>what have you urged that I cannot r.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 787" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 787</bibl></cit>. '<cit><quote>tis so, I cannot r. it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.241" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 241</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>r. my allegation, if you can,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 40</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to reprehend, to blame: <bibl n="shak. luc 242" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 242</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 142.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 142, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.153" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.223" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 223</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.148" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.189" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 189</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 11, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 95</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>